cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.LG 

The paper proposes a model for representing multimedia scenarios with interactive events using the Non-deterministic Timed Concurrent Constraint (ntcc) calculus. This involves formalizing temporal relations and conditional branching. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the most likely category as it deals with formalisms and models for programming languages. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with interactive events and conditional branching. The use of ntcc also suggests that the paper may belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. The paper deals with multimedia scenarios (cs.MM) and interactive events, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
